<h1>Questions About Subscribing</h1>
    <h3>Do I need to have an account to use BBN?<h3>
      <p>BBN allows unregistered users to browse limited versions of the company profiles and projects posted on the site. In order to see complete project listings, post a project or bid on an existing project, you must sign up for an account, either as a Developer[LINK] or Contractor[LINK].</p>
    <h3>What account types are available on BBN?/How much does it cost to subscribe to BBN?</h3>
      <p>There are two types of accounts on BBN - Developer accounts and Contractor accounts.</p>
      <p>Developer subscriptions are free, but do not allow bidding on projects. Contractor subscriptions cost a nominal $XX per year and allow bidding on projects.</p>
    <h3>How do I register for BBN?<h3>
      <p>If you are a Developer[LINK] follow this link to the Developer Registration page. If you are a Contractor[LINK] follow this link to the Contractor Registration page.</p>
      <p>After you're registered, you'll receive an email from BBN asking you to activate your account. Then you're ready to set up a profile and jump into the central marketplace of the building industry.</p>
