  <h2>Questions About My Account</h2>
    <h3>What is a profile?</h3>
      <p>Profiles are descriptions of a company and its areas of expertise. They are important in allowing other members to find your company, see your successes and make contact with you. To access your profile, go to your account homepage or search for your company's name.</p>
    <h3>Who can see my BBN profile?</h3>
      <p>Anyone searching the BBN site can see your company's name, general areas of business and other basic information such as number of projects you have posted or been involved in. Only other BBN members can see your full company profile, bid on or invite you to bid on a project or send you personal messages using the BBN service. Since BBN is a business service, we do not differentiate among various levels of internal privacy or connectedness. Anything you post to your profile can be seen by any other BBN client.</p>
    <h3>What parts of my profile can be viewed on the BBN website?</h3>
      <p>When you press the Save Changes button at the bottom of your Edit Profile page or at the bottom of the Create Profile page during account registration, any text or images you have put on that page can be viewed on your public profile. These materials can be changed by you at any time by editing your profile as described below[LINK].</p>
    <h3>How do I change my account type?</h3>
      <p>If you would like to change a Contractor account to a Developer account or vice versa, please submit an Account Change form found here[LINK].<p>
