    <h3>How do I deactivate my account?[WHAT IS THE ACTUAL SYSTEM?]</h3>
      <strong>To deactivate your account:</strong>
        <ol>
          <li>Go to your Profile Page.</li>
          <li>Click on Account Settings.</li>
          <li>Select Account Status.</li>
          <li>Click on Deactivate Account.</li>
        </ol>
      <p>When you deactivate your account, your profile and all information associated with it (including active projects or active bids) disappears from the BBN site immediately. Other BBN users will not be able to search for or view any of your information.</p>
      <p>If you'd like to return to BBN later, you can reactivate your account by logging in with your email and password and selecting one of our standard membership options. Your profile will be completely restored. You will need to have access to the login email address and a valid credit card in order to reactivate your account.</p>
    <h3>How can I delete my BBN account?</h3>
      <p>Normally, you would simply deactivate your account if you stop using BBN. This removes your company's information from the BBN site and makes it so that BBN users can no longer search for your company, see your profile or view any information associated with that profile.</p>
      <p>In case you want to make use of BBN again, we save your information so that it is easy for you to reactivate your account. However, if you think that you will not use the service again or the company has gone out of business and you would like your account deleted, first deactivate your account through the Account Settings, then by using this form[LINK] request that BBN permanently delete your account information with no option for future recovery.</p>
