    <h3>How do I know an email is from BBN?</h3>
      <p>BBN protects its clients. Any emails from BBN which contain a link will always direct you to our website and will never ask for sensitive information such as Social Security Number or bank account information. We will never ask you to randomly change your password or to verify your credit card number for an account. If there is a problem, we will contact you through the in-site messaging system so that you can access our message in the security of the site.</p>
  <h2>Questions About Creating a Project</h2>
    <h3>How do I create a new project?</h3>
      <p>Developer accounts can create new projects for bidding. To do so, you: </p>
        <ol>
          <li>Sign in to your account.</li>
          <li>From your Homepage/Profile page, click the Post a Project link in the upper right corner of the page.</li>
          <li>Fill out the information on the Post a Project page.</li>
          <li>Click the Save and Continue button at the bottom.</li>
        </ol>
      <p>Only invite bidders when you are sure the project description is complete.</p>
      <p>Tip: By setting the Open for Bidding date later than you are actually planning to open bidding, then saving your changes, you can come back to the project to make further edits before it is visible to bidders.</p>  
    <h3>Can I create a project, but wait to activate/post it?</h3>
      <p>You can create a project, but post it later by selecting a later Open for Bidding date in the Project Timeline section of the Post a Project screen. Any Open for Bidding date can be selected, even years later, allowing you to activate the posting at any time you choose by later editing the project and adjusting the Open for Bidding date to the desired date/time. However, once a project is Open for Bidding, you can only Cancel the project or put it On Hold, not make it "inactive" again.</p>
    <h3>How do I invite specific contractors to bid on a project?</h3>
      <p>After a project has been posted, you can invite specific contractors to bid on it either by individually inviting them from their profile pages with the Invite to Bid link at the right of their company name, or you can invite a group of them by:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Go to the project page.</li>
          <li>In the bottom right corner there is a list of Other Contractors in Project Area.</li>
          <li>Click the Invite to Bid link next to each contractor you'd like to add.</li>
        </ol>
    <h3>Can I limit the contractors bidding on a project?</h3>
      <p>You can disallow individual contractors from bidding on your project by:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Sign in to your account.</li>
          <li>Go to the contractor's profile page.</li>
          <li>Under the contractor's profile image, click the Ignore button.</li>
        </ol>
      <p>This will prevent the contractor from bidding on your projects in the future. </p>
      <p>It is impossible to limit contractors able to view a project to only a handful as it is advantageous for more contractors to bid on a project. The BBN mission is to improve the marketplace for contractors and developers by making it centralized and inclusive. </p>
    <h3>Can I invite additional contractors once a project has been posted?</h3>
      <p>Once you have posted a project, you can invite additional contractors to bid on that project either  with the Invite to Bid function on their company's profile page or by:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Go to the project page.</li>
          <li>In the bottom right corner there is a list of Other Contractors in Project Area.</li>
          <li>Click the Invite to Bid link next to each contractor you'd like to add.</li>
        </ol>
     <p>This feature allows you to invite additional contractors to bid until the end of the bid submission period.</p>
