    <h3>Can I delay a project once it's been posted if the project status changes?</h3>
      <p>You can change the status of a project to "On Hold" by:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Go to the project page.</li>
          <li>Click the Edit button.</li>
          <li>In the Project Timeline section, check the box marked "This Project is On Hold."</li>
          <li>Click the Save Changes button at the bottom of the page.</li>
        </ol>
      <p>Please only put a project on hold if there is some expectation that it will be reactivated in the next 12 months. You can later go back into the project description and change the bid submission period using the normal calendar. If a project is unlikely to be reactivated within the next 12 months, instead consider Cancelling the project.</p>
    <h3>How do I cancel a project once it has been posted?</h3>
      <p>If a project must be cancelled for any reason, you can do so by:</p> 
        <ol>
          <li>Go to the project page.</li>
          <li>In the Project Timeline section, click the Cancel Project button.</li>
          <li>You will then be prompted to confirm that you want to cancel the project.</li>
        </ol>
