      <p>Each project is placed into a particular credit tier based on the project owner's estimated budget for the project. These tiers are: </p>
      <p>Tier 1: XX-XX</p>
      <p>Tier 2: XX-XX</p>
      <p>Tier 3: XX-XX</p>
      <p>Tier 4: XX-XX</p>
      <p>Tier 5: XX-XX</p>
      <p>For contractors to submit a bid for a project in a particular tier, they must spend a number of credits proportionate to the value of the project tier. XX credits for Tier 1 projects, XX credits for Tier 2 projects, XX credits for Tier 3 projects, XX credits for Tier 4 projects and XX credits for Tier 5 projects. This ensures that the cost for submitting a bid is related to the actual value of the project being bid upon rather than an arbitrary flat rate.</p> 
    <h3>How do I buy credits?</h3>
      </p>To buy credits:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Sign in to your account.</li>
          <li>In the upper right corner of any page, click on the Buy Credits link.</li>
          <li>Select whether you wish to buy a single credit or a block of credits.</li>
          <li>Enter your payment information.</li>
        </ol> 
    <h3>Do I need to buy credits all at once?</h3>
      <p>New EPS users may wish to purchase credits only when they want to bid on a project until they have a better sense of the number of credits they will need for a particular time period such as quarterly or annually. Credits can be purchased at any time.</p> 
    <h3>Can I be refunded for credits I have already purchased if I cancel my membership?</h3>
      <p>If you deactivate your membership, any credits belonging to your company's account are put on hold along with the rest of your profile information. BBN can not refund the cash value of purchased credits once they are purchased, so it is most useful to bid on projects before deactivating your account if you have extra credits in your bank. </p<>
    <h3>How do I bid on a project?</h3>
      <p>To bid on a project:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Go to the project description page.<li>
          <li>Click on the Create a Bid button on the right side of the project title bar.</li>
          <li>Begin entering information on your bid.</li>
          <li>When you are finished entering your bid information, click the Submit Bid button. You may store a draft of your information on the site as described below.</li> 
        </ol>
    <h3>Can I save a draft of my bid proposal or do I have to enter all the information at once?<h3>
      <p>You may store a draft of your bid submission on the site, allowing you to work on a bid in multiple sessions[BY DOING A THING]. When you are finished with the bid submission, simply click the Submit Bid button at the bottom of the Create a Bid page. You can also fill in a bid submission with information from a previous bid, by [DOING A THING].</p>
    <h3>Can I change my bid proposal once I have submitted it?</h3>
      <p>You are free to change your bid proposal once it has been submitted as long as it is before the submission deadline by: </p>
        <ol>
          <li>Sign into your account.</li>
          <li>From your homepage/profile page click the Track My Bids link in the upper right corner.</li>
          <li>Select the project from your bid list.</li>
          <li>Click on the Edit My Bid link.</li>
          <li>When you have made your desired changes, click the Save Changes button at the bottom of the page.</li>
        </ol>
    <h3>OR</h3>
      <p>Once a bid has been submitted you can not go back and make changes, even if it is before the end of the submission period. Make sure that you have made any changes to your bid draft before you submit it.</p>
  <h2>Questions About the Project/Bidding Process<h2> 
    <h3>When is a winning bidder selected?</h3>
      <p>A winning bidder is selected XX[30?] days after the bid submission period ends. Individual project owners may announce a winning bidder before the XX day period ends at their discretion. </p>
    <h3>What happens if a project owner fails to select a winning bidder?</h3>
      <p>If a project owner fails completely to select a winning bidder for a project, BBN refunds credits spent on the bidding process to the bidders. We also contact the project owner to see why no bidder was selected as a winner.<p>
    <h3>What happens if a project is canceled after bidding has begun/bids have been submitted?</h3>
      <p>If a project owner cancels a project, BBN refunds credits spent on the bidding process to the bidders.</p>
    <h3>What happens if a project is put on hold after bidding has begun/bids have been submitted?</h3>
      <p>If a project owner places a project On Hold, no new bids can be submitted for the project. Bids can be prepared for the project and saved on BBN, but will not be able to be finalized until the project is no longer On Hold. Bids that have already been submitted are saved in their current format. When the project is reactivated, they can be edited as per normal. If a project that is On Hold is Canceled by the project owner, credits spent on bid submissions will be refunded to the bidder as for any other canceled project.</p>  
